Additional Terms for Modified Versions

This implementation includes modifications and enhancements to the original
NIST reference implementation. These modifications are also released under
the same public domain terms as the original NIST software.

Modifications include:
- Unified multi-level security implementation (128, 192, 256-bit)
- OpenSSL BIGNUM constant-time backend
- HKDF key derivation function (RFC 5869)
- Comprehensive test suite and security hardening
- Fuzz testing and timing analysis infrastructure

The authors of these modifications disclaim all copyright interest and
dedicate their contributions to the public domain.
